    <refsect1 id="description"><title>Description</title>
        <para>
			Built-in work-item functions can be used to query the number of dimensions, the global and local work size specified to <citerefentry><refentrytitle>clEnqueueNDRangeKernel</refentrytitle></citerefentry>, and the global and local identifier of each work-item when this kernel is being executed on a device. The number of dimensions, the global and local work size when executing a kernel using the function <citerefentry><refentrytitle>clEnqueueTask</refentrytitle></citerefentry> is one.
        </para>
    </refsect1>
	
